 wider debates about the place of history writing in medieval culture, textuality and manuscript transmission. SUSAN B. EDGINGTON is a Teaching and Research Fellow at Queen Mary University of London; STEVEN J. BIDDLECOMBE edited the Latin text of Baldric's Historia (2014); having taught at a number of universities, most recently at NottinghamTrent; he is currently an independent scholar.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and other religionsxIslamxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aChristianityyTo 1500. 0aChurch historyy11th century. 0aCrusadesvEarly works to 1800yFirst, 1096-1099. 0aCrusadesvSourcesyFirst, 1096-1099. 0aCrusadesyFirst, 1096-1099vEarly works to 1800. 0aCrusadesyFirst, 1096-1099vSources. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAntioch.  aBaldric of Bourgueil.  aDorylaeum.  aFirst Crusade.  aHistoria Ierosolimitana.  aHoly Sepulchre.  aJerusalem.  ahistory of the crusades.  amedieval chronicles.  amedieval history writing.1 aBiddlecombe, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdgington, Susan B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311143101740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787444539?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787444539423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787444539/original  a978-3-11-143101-7  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles